<span id="freeTextContainer18379757841047501200">Her name is Our Lady of the Tears. She&apos;s a small, crumbling Baroque church in the heart of Seville, Spain. And at least one person -- a computer hacker nicknamed Vespers -- believes that she kills to defend herself. In Arturo Perez-Reverte&apos;s stylish and entertaining <i>The Seville Communion</i>, Rome sends handsome Father Lorenzo Quart to investigate. He meets a feisty parish pri</span>
  <span id="freeText18379757841047501200" style="display:none">Her name is Our Lady of the Tears. She's a small, crumbling Baroque church in the heart of Seville, Spain. And at least one person -- a computer hacker nicknamed Vespers -- believes that she kills to defend herself. In Arturo Perez-Reverte's stylish and entertaining <i>The Seville Communion</i>, Rome sends handsome Father Lorenzo Quart to investigate. He meets a feisty parish priest, a beautiful aristocrat, an ambitious banker, and three of the most touching, wonderfully ineffectual crooks to ever dabble in a life of crime. There are mysteries as well, from another death at the church to the secrets of the human heart. <br />-- Nancy Pate</span>
